{
  "stem": "3848.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I used to get sick every year at a special time in May, with malaria.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I must have got that someplace over there, and it is a very bad sickness.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was a small hospital there, very small, and I was there for a month each year at the special time.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The attacks used to come every second day.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I used to shake, develop a temperature, and after that, quiet again.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that would be every second day with the shaking and cold, and no blanket was good enough to cover up, and then temperature, and then quiet again.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that's the sickness of malaria.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The medication that I used to get was quinine.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Quinine is a terrible medication because it's bitter.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It's so bitter that no matter what you eat you always taste the quinine.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I developed a little pill for myself.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I used to rub the quinine into a little package of cigarette paper, and swallowed the whole thing through there so it shouldn't affect my throat.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And that's how I developed my own invention-- how to take a pill.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "In this particular town-- a small thing and I'm going to make it short, that food was not enough.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I had a bed, and my uncle had a bed.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And one day we decided to sell to the Cossack people the mattress, the cover, of one of our beds and the blanket and the sheet-- we had one sheet.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The mattress was just a cover and straw was inside.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So when we decided to sell one, we had enough food for the stuff for one day for ourselves.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We ate enough that day, but then we had to sleep together in one small bed for a long, long time, just for one day of food.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
